Have teenage pregnancies in Kenya increased due to Covid-19 containment measures?

:bar_chart: Data from multiple sources does not seem to support claims of such a surge: https://t.co/84nNpOulP2
text.1:
How many Kenyans are employed formally in the agricultural sector?

:tractor: We looked into a claim that 294,000 Kenyans hold formal jobs in agriculture and found it to be mostly true: https://t.co/dpYIihqTkX
text.2:
How accurate is the claim by President Uhuru Kenyatta that Kenya’s economy grew by 4.6% in the first quarter of 2020?

:chart_increasing: The data we looked at showed the claim to be mostly true: https://t.co/AFAuR0xuRr
text.3:
How true is a claim that 70% of Kenyans are Christians but the country still ranks as one of the most corrupt nations globally?

While it's true that Kenya is one of the world's most corrupt countries, the claim that 70% of Kenyans are Christians is false: https://t.co/dLwnSdGnsm
text.4:
How accurate is the claim shared on the Aramide Health Tips Facebook page that bananas are a remedy for many human illnesses and conditions?

:magnifying_glass_tilted_right: We looked at several scientific studies and found the claim to be mostly true: https://t.co/a27mzzajyc
